Endpoints.Name: Continent by ID
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
The Continents endpoint helps you with assigning Countries and Leagues to the part of the world (Continent) they belong to. 
Available Continents are Europe, Asia, Africa, Oceania, North America and South America.

Especially if you want to show many Leagues on your website/app, this might be a useful endpoint for you.

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```countries```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

Endpoints.Name: All Countries
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
The Countries endpoint provides you Country information like for example its Flag, IsoCode, Continent and other related Country information.

The Countries endpoint also helps you with assigning Leagues to the Country they belong to. 
If for example, you want to show the Leagues per Country on your website/app, this might be a useful endpoint for you by using the Leagues Include. 

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```leagues``` ```continent```

**Filters**
------
```name``` ```continent_id```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

TestCases.Description:
**Introduction**
------
The Countries endpoint provides you Country information like for example its Flag, IsoCode, Continent and other related Country information.

The Countries endpoint also helps you with assigning Leagues to the Country they belong to. 
If for example, you want to show the Leagues per Country on your website/app, this might be a useful endpoint for you by using the Leagues Include. 

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```leagues``` ```continent```

**Filters**
------
```name``` ```continent_id```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

Endpoints.Name: Country by ID
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
The Countries endpoint provides you Country information like for example its Flag, IsoCode, Continent and other related Country information.

The Countries endpoint also helps you with assigning Leagues to the Country they belong to. 
If for example, you want to show the Leagues per Country on your website/app, this might be a useful endpoint for you by using the Leagues Include. 

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```leagues``` ```continent```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

Endpoints.Name: All Leagues
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
The Leagues endpoint is for most customers the starting point. 
A request on this endpoint would return a response with all Leagues you have access to, based on the plan you are subscribed to.

The Leagues endpoint provides you League information like its ID, Name, Country, Coverage etc.

The endpoint is often used in combination with the Season or Seasons Includes. 
Where the Season include returns information about the active Season only, the Seasons Include returns information about all seasons available for the specific Leagues.  

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```season``` ```seasons``` ```country```

**Filters**
------
```name``` ```country_id```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

Endpoints.Name: All Seasons
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
Responses of the Seasons endpoint are limited to Seasons of the Leagues available in the Plan you are subscribed to. 
Responses provide you details about for example the Season ID, Name, League ID, Year and if the Season is Active Yes or No.

One of the main features of the Seasons endpoint is the ability to retrieve full Season Games, (history) Fixtures, Results or Upcoming Fixtures. 
This can be achieved by using the proper Includes which are listed in the section Endpoint Details.  

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```league``` ```stages``` ```standings``` ```fixtures``` ```teams```

**Filters**
------
```name``` ```league_id```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

Endpoints.Name: Fixture by ID
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
The Fixtures endpoint provides information about Games in particular Leagues. 
There are always 2 teams involved in a Fixture. For many customers, Fixtures is the main endpoint for their app/website. 
Be aware your access is limited to Fixtures of Leagues, available in the Plan you are subscribed to.

Responses of the Fixture endpoint are highly customizable, because there are many Includes available to extend the response. 
Requests often start with the Includes localTeam and VisitorTeam. 
Events, Stats, Lineups, Comment, Trends etc. are often added as well.

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------

```balls``` ```odds``` ```runs``` ```bowling``` ```batting``` ```venue``` ```stage``` ```season``` ```league``` ```visitorteam``` ```localteam``` ```scoreboards``` ```firstumpire``` ```secondumpire``` ```referee``` ```manofseries``` ```manofmatch``` ```tosswon```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

application/json.Example:
{
  "data": {
    "resource": "fixtures",
    "id": 3,
    "league_id": 3,
    "season_id": 6,
    "stage_id": 1755,
    "round": "2nd T20I",
    "localteam_id": 40,
    "visitorteam_id": 41,
    "starting_at": "2018-10-12T16:00:00.000000Z",
    "type": "T20I",
    "live": false,
    "status": "Finished",
    "last_period": null,
    "note": "South Africa won by 6 wickets (with 26 balls remaining)",
    "venue_id": 96,
    "toss_won_team_id": 41,
    "winner_team_id": 40,

Endpoints.Name: Team by ID
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
With the Teams endpoint you can find all Team Details you need. 
You can think if information about when the Team is founded, Logo, Team Name, Short Name etc.

But especially by using the right includes you can have the right Team details you need, like the Team Coach, Team Venues, Results, Upcoming Games, Team Stats and many more valuable Team details.

**Good to know**
------
> The squad include only returns the squad for the team of the active season in the domestic main league the team is playing in. 
For international teams it will return the teams as is.

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```country``` ```results``` ```fixtures``` ```squad```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

TestCases.Name: All Teams
TestCases.Description:
**Introduction**
------
With the Teams endpoint you can find all Team Details you need. 
You can think if information about when the Team is founded, Logo, Team Name, Short Name etc.

But especially by using the right includes you can have the right Team details you need, like the Team Coach, Team Venues, Results, Upcoming Games, Team Stats and many more valuable Team details.

**Good to know**
------
> The squad include only returns the squad for the team of the active season in the domestic main league the team is playing in. 
For international teams it will return the teams as is.

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__10__ - You can add a max of __10__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```country``` ```results``` ```fixtures``` ```squad```

**Filters**
------
```name``` ```country_id```

**Sorting**
------
You can sort on all fields.

Endpoints.Name: Global Team Rankings
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
Global team ranking is available for all plans. even if the underlaying leagues are not accessible for your subscription.

By default this endpoint will return information for ```men``` and ```women``` about ```TEST```, ```ODI``` and ```T20I``` tournament types. 
You can easily filter this to only the gender and type you are interested in. 

**Good to know**
------
> Add &filter[tournament_type]=TEST&filter[gender]=men to only get men's TEST results.

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__1__ - You can add a max of __1__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```teams```

TestCases.Name: Global Team Rankings
TestCases.Description:
**Introduction**
------
Global team ranking is available for all plans. even if the underlaying leagues are not accessible for your subscription.

By default this endpoint will return information for ```men``` and ```women``` about ```TEST```, ```ODI``` and ```T20I``` tournament types. 
You can easily filter this to only the gender and type you are interested in. 

**Good to know**
------
> Add &filter[tournament_type]=TEST&filter[gender]=men to only get men's TEST results.

**Pagination**
------
__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__1__ - You can add a max of __1__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
```teams```

Scores objects are related to ball by ball comments and batting records.

**Introduction**
------
Scores objects are related to ball by ball comments and batting records. 
With this endpoint you are able to get a list of all scores.

__NO__ - Indicates if this endpoint contains pagination.

**Nested Includes**
------
__0__ - You can add a max of __0__ levels of nested includes.

**Includes Options**
------
No includes available for this endpoint.

------
Batting scoreboards can be divided into ```S1```, ```S2```, ```S3```, ```S4``` (S3 and S4 only for test matches).

A bowling record will contain data about ```fout_x```, ```six_x```, ```score```, ```ball```, ```player```, ```team``` and much more.

------
No nested relationships available for this endpoint.

**Parameters**
------
No nested relationships available for this endpoint.

Parameters.Name: include
Parameters.Description: One or a comma separated list of relationships to include.

Endpoints.Name: Player Career Stats
Endpoints.Description:
**Introduction**
------
Interesting information for a lot of purposes is the progression of a player during a season. 
We calculate statistics like ```bowling strike rate```, ```batting strike rate```, ```runs```, ```wickets```, ```medians```, ```economy rate``` and a lot more on a per season basis. 
This gives you great insight in how the player did during a season and gives powerful information for your fantasy game also.

------
